Library Preparation

Once the IP quality has been validated, the ChIP material is converted into an Illumina Sequencing library. This is done using the NEBNext Ultra II DNA Library Prep Kit for Illumina (NEB #E7645S/L).

Prior consideration

  • ChIPed material should be in volume of 50 L 10mM Tris-HCl pH8.0 and be in a PCR tube
  • For the input: use 40-50 ng
  • For the IP material, use the whole sample (usually a few ng). If the QuBit did not permit the quantification of the ChIP material (concentration too low), it can still be converted into a sequencing library, provided that the qPCR validations are OK.
Figure - Overview of the library Preparation protocol
Source: https://international.neb.com

End-repair

  1. Adjust the volume of the IPs and Input material to a total volume of 50L with 10mM Tris-HCl pH8.0, then add:

    • (green) 3L NEBNext UltraII End Prep Enzyme Mix
    • (green) 7L NEBNext UltraII End Prep Reaction Buffer

  2. Set a 200L pipette to 50L and then pipette the entire volume up and down at least 10 times to mix thoroughly.

  3. Perform a quick spin in a mini centrifuge

  4. Place tubes in a PCR machine and run the following program, with the lid set at 75C

    • 30 min at 20C
    • 30 min at 65C
    • hold 4C

STOP point: If necessary, samples can be stored at -20C; however, a slight loss in yield (~20%) may be observed. NEB recommends continuing with adaptor ligation before stopping

Adapter ligation

Beforehand: Dilute the NEBNext Adaptor for Illumina with the adaptor dilution buffer (10mM Tris pH8.0, 10mM NaCl) as recommended in the table below:

DNA quantity Adaptor Dilution Working adaptor concentration
1g - 100ng No dilution 15M
100ng - 5ng 10-fold (1:10) 1.5M
less than 5ng 25-fold (1:25) 0.6M

NB: The NEBNext Adaptor for Illumina is provided in the Multiplex Oligo kit (7335S et 7500S)

  1. Mix the (red) NEBNext Ultra II Ligation Master Mix by pipetting up and down several times

  2. To the 60L End-repaired material, add the following:

    • (red) 30L NEBNext Ultra II Ligation Master Mix
    • (red) 1L NEBNext Ligation Enhancer
    • (red) 2.5L (diluted) NEBNext Adaptor for Illumina

  3. Set a 200L pipette to 50L and then pipette the entire volume up and down at least 10 times to mix thoroughly. Caution, the Ligation Master Mix is very viscous.

  4. Quickly spin in a mini centrifuge

  5. Incubate 20 min at 20C in PCR machine (with the LID OFF)

  6. Add (red) 3L USER Enzyme to the ligation mixture. NB: The USER enzyme is provided in the Multiplex Oligo kit

  7. Mix well by gentle pipetting up and down at least 10 times

  8. Perform a quick spin in a mini centrifuge

  9. Place tubes in PCR machine and incubate for 20 min at 37C with the LID set at > 47C.

STOP point: samples can be stored overnight at -20C

Clean-UP using Ampure XP beads

  1. Warm the Ampure XP beads to room temperature for 30 min. Prepare fresh 80% EtOH. Transfer the adaptor ligated material to a 1.5mL DNA LoBind Eppendorf microtube.

  2. Mix the beads well by vortexing (> 10s) and precisely add 0.9 volume (= 87L) of Ampure XP beads to adapter ligated material

  3. Mix by pipetting up and down at least 10 times followed by vortexing

  4. Incubate 5 min at RT

  5. Quickly spin in a mini centrifuge / normal centrifuge

  6. Place tubes on magnetic particle separator.

  7. After 5 minutes (or when the solution is clear) discard the supernatant

  8. Keep tubes on magnet and add 200L freshly prepared 80% EtOH to the beads

  9. Incubate 1 min at RT while the tubes are still on the magnetic rack

  10. Discard supernatant. Do not disturb the beads

  11. Keep tube on magnet and add again 200L 80% EtOH

  12. Incubate 1 min at RT.

  13. Discard supernatant. Do not disturb the beads.

  14. Do a short spin (2-3 sec), then place the tube on magnet and aspirate remaining EtOH with a p20. Leave the tube on magnet for 30 sec (lid open to air-dry). Proceed to the following step (= elution) when the beads are still dark brown and glossy looking (and all liquid has evaporated). When the beads turn lighter brown and start to crack, they are too dry and the elution becomes inefficient.

  15. Remove the tube from magnet and quickly add 16L Bottled water.

  16. Mix by pipetting up and down at least 10 times.

  17. Incubate 2 min at RT.

  18. Quickly spin the tube

  19. Place tube on magnetic particle separator for 5min at RT

  20. Transfer 15L of the supernatant to a fresh PCR tube. Avoid taking beads at all cost.

Samples can be stored at -20C.

PCR amplification

Prior starting: plan the experiment to use a unique index for all the libraries that will be sequenced together

  1. Add to the 15L cleaned-up adapter ligated material the following:

    • (blue) 25L NEBNext Ultra II Q5 Master Mix
    • (blue) 5L Index 10M primer
    • (blue) 5L Universal 10M PCR primer

  2. Set a 200L pipette to 40L and then pipette the entire volume up and down at least 10 times to mix thoroughly. Quickly spin in a mini-centrifuge.

  3. Place tubes in PCR machine and run the following program

    • 30 sec @ 98C
    • 10 sec @ 98C |
    • 75 sec @ 65C | x (7 - 12 cycles)
    • 5 min @ 72C
    • hold 4C

    The number of cycles depends on the starting quantity.

    • If starting with 5ng, do 12 cycles
    • If starting with 10ng, do 11 cycles
    • If starting with 20ng, do 10 cycles
    • If starting with 50ng, do 8 cycles

Clean up of PCR amplified library

Clean up the PCR amplified library using Ampure XP beads. Two procedures can be followed. Do either one or the other.

a- Purification without size selection. To do so, add 1 volume of Ampure XP beads the the PCR amplified material and follow the procedure done for the purification of Adapter-Ligated material. Elute in 20L.

b- Purification with size selection. To do so, place 100 ng of PCR amplified material in a new DNA LoBind tube and adjust the volume to 50L with H2O. Then, do a double-size selection (0.6X - 0.9X). Elute in 12L.

Quantification

Quantify 2L of cleaned-up material using QuBit dsDNA HS kit. Follow the procedure shown in the QuBit section.
